  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "29c4750c-f3ba-8077-8f7e-eb1f618bbf47",
      "heading": "Summary Table REC",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Recommender System Type",
          "Target of Recommendation",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Initialization Method",
          "Updates to Recommendations",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Recommendation types",
          "Evaluation",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "MOOC",
          "E-Learning",
          "Hybrid",
          "Exterrnal Learning Resources",
          "31 post-graduate students",
          "1 Computer Science Course",
          "– Lecture slides (concept text, extracted keyphrases)\n\n– Student DNU feedback logs \n\n– External APIs (Wikipedia + YouTube)",
          "– Personal Knowledge Graph (PKG) nodes initialized from lecture concepts\n\n – Concept & resource embeddings via SBERT (all-MiniLM-L6-v2) \n\n– Relation weights set using cosine similarity",
          "– PKG updated each time a learner flags new DNU concepts \n\n– Concept and neighbor embeddings re-propagated through LightGCN layers \n\n– Re-ranking by similarity between learner-PKG and resource graph",
          "– Keyphrase extraction: SingleRank + DBpedia Spotlight – Entity linking: Wikipedia/DBpedia URIs \n\n– Text normalized, stop-word removed \n\n– SBERT embeddings generated for slides & external texts \n\n– Graph edges built: {relatedTo, subcategoryOf, hasCategory}",
          "Top-N external resources",
          "Online\n{Precision@5: 0.68 - PKG-Keyphrase, MAP: 0.78 - PKG-Keyphrase, MRR: 0.81:  - PKG-Keyphrase}",
          "– Introduces Personal Knowledge Graphs (PKGs) that learners build themselves by marking DNU concepts. \n\n– Combines semantic embeddings (SBERT) with graph propagation (LightGCN) for richer contextual recommendations. \n\n– Transparent & scrutable learner model: students can see and edit their PKG. \n\n– Demonstrates significant improvements in accuracy and user trust compared to content-only approaches.",
          "– Small sample size (N = 31, 1 course). \n\n– Concept extraction errors (e.g., non-academic or ambiguous terms). \n\n– YouTube API limit restricts query length (≤ 5 concepts). \n\n– No direct measurement of learning gain. \n\n– Manual DNU entry burden on learners; automation needed for scale."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
