    {
      "id": "1b34750c-f3ba-801a-adce-f09bc4ad1b8d",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The knowledge graph is created from users labelling contents as “did not understand” as they interact with the materials. This labelling is a precursor for the construction of the learner model and uses this representation to suggest external learning resources. The approach is tested on a sample of 31 students and shows promising results on user-centred metrics such as accuracy, novelty, diversity, usefulness, satisfaction and intentions. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1b34750c-f3ba-801a-adce-f09bc4ad1b8d",
        "parent": {
